they would throw you out
with the phone.

242
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:08,840
Is this your father's kingdom?

243
00:18:08,960 --> 00:18:09,840
Are you trying to scare me?

244
00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:10,960
Are you threatening me?

245
00:18:14,640 --> 00:18:15,640
Meenamma!

246
00:18:21,680 --> 00:18:23,960
Enough! This is too much.

247
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:28,520
You have made me so angry that
I will sit down.

248
00:18:29,800 --> 00:18:32,800
And if I sit down don't think
I won't be able to stand up again.

249
00:18:32,880 --> 00:18:35,120
And if I stand up don't think...

250
00:18:35,240 --> 00:18:36,520
I cannot sit down again.

251
00:18:42,560 --> 00:18:45,200
And I forgive you for the mobile too.

252
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:47,160
I can buy the entire mobile company
if I want to.

253
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:50,960
4G, 5G! I have a lot of money.

254
00:18:51,840 --> 00:18:53,000
Poor people.

255
00:19:10,240 --> 00:19:11,360
Brother, show me your ticket.

256
00:19:12,280 --> 00:19:13,080
No.

257
00:19:13,200 --> 00:19:14,600
What no?

258
00:19:16,800 --> 00:19:19,560
If you don't have a ticket
then you will have to pay a fine.

259
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:26,880
I have my ticket.

260
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,680
This is a ticket.

261
00:19:30,760 --> 00:19:32,400
If you don't have a ticket
then you will have to pay a fine.

262
00:19:32,520 --> 00:19:33,360
From where have you boarded the train?

263
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:34,400
Are they with you?

264
00:19:34,480 --> 00:19:36,880
<i>Listen to me very carefully TC</i>

265
00:19:37,040 --> 00:19:39,840
<i>Don't take it easy on these hooligans</i>

266
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:49,920
<i>I swear all four of them
Are carrying long weapons</i>

267
00:19:51,800 --> 00:19:56,800
<i>These four friends have abducted this girl
And taking her very far</i>

268
00:19:57,440 --> 00:19:58,840
<i>Very carefully</i>

269
00:20:02,400 --> 00:20:03,720
Come on, get up.

270
00:20:04,360 --> 00:20:05,760
Come with me.

271
00:20:05,840 --> 00:20:06,640
Come on.

272
00:20:12,440 --> 00:20:15,000
Now you will be in trouble.

273
00:20:15,120 --> 00:20:17,680
You can go to jail and
play ping pong!

274
00:20:17,800 --> 00:20:20,040
You think you are King Kong?

275
00:20:21,000 --> 00:20:22,160
What?

276
00:20:25,720 --> 00:20:26,720
Why aren't you answering?

277
00:20:27,280 --> 00:20:30,280
And Meenamma,
you are on my watch now.

278
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:32,160
The TC is on our side.

279
00:20:32,680 --> 00:20:34,640
See how he teaches them a lesson!

280
00:20:51,280 --> 00:20:52,320
Enough!

281
00:20:53,000 --> 00:20:54,080
This is too much.

282
00:20:54,840 --> 00:20:59,000
You all have made me so angry that now
I have to sit.

283
00:21:00,680 --> 00:21:02,800
You sing and dance.

284
00:21:02,960 --> 00:21:05,400
We are going by Chennai Express.

285
00:21:05,800 --> 00:21:09,120
You laugh and cry.
We are going by Chennai Express.

286
00:21:12,040 --> 00:21:12,960
Meenamma?

287
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:16,840
Whatever happened with the TC,
you are the solo witness to it.

288
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:20,760
That is why you will come with us
to Komban village on Chennai Express.

289
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:22,920
On Chennai Express!

290
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,440
<i>All my wishes were washed away
with the ashes.</i>

291
00:21:46,920 --> 00:21:50,480
<i>I had come to Goa to immerse the ashes
but instead drowned the TC.</i>

292
00:21:50,720 --> 00:21:53,760
<i>My friends tried
to get in touch with me.</i>

293
00:21:53,840 --> 00:21:55,160
<i>But they could not track me down because</i>

294
00:21:55,240 --> 00:21:59,200
<i>My 35,000 rupees cell phone
was lying somewhere on a railway track.</i>

295
00:22:36,400 --> 00:22:37,520
I want to sleep.

296
00:22:37,600 --> 00:22:38,720
You sleep.

297
00:22:39,200 --> 00:22:42,080
Periyanna, check on the next station.

298
00:22:42,200 --> 00:22:43,160
I am hungry.

299
00:22:43,280 --> 00:22:44,120
Okay.

300
00:22:50,240 --> 00:22:51,320
Meenamma...

301
00:22:52,920 --> 00:22:53,760
What is happening?

302
00:22:54,040 --> 00:22:55,520
I cannot understand a thing.

303
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:56,560
You are scolding your kidnappers

304
00:22:56,640 --> 00:22:58,240
And they are listening to you!

305
00:23:01,440 --> 00:23:04,040
I will clear your confusion.

306
00:23:16,640 --> 00:23:19,640
My father is a highly respected man
in the Komban area.

307
00:23:21,160 --> 00:23:22,960
He is a... You know, <i>Periyathalai</i>?

308
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:25,880
<i>Periyathalai?</i> You mean teacher?

309
00:23:26,480 --> 00:23:27,520
No.

310
00:23:28,200 --> 00:23:29,200
Don.

311
00:23:31,160 --> 00:23:34,240
These four are listening
to my <i>pechi</i> because...

312
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:35,200
<i>Pechi?</i>

313
00:23:35,440 --> 00:23:37,360
- Chatter.
- Chatter! Oh, I get it.

314
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:41,600
So they were listening to me because
they're my father's goons.

315
00:23:41,720 --> 00:23:44,600
Goons?

316
00:23:56,120 --> 00:24:01,200
My father asked them to kidnap me
and bring me back to Komban.

317
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:04,680
That means your father
is Godfather of the South.

318
00:24:06,160 --> 00:24:08,240
And he wants my <i>Kalyanam</i> to be done.

319
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:09,400
Kal...

320
00:24:11,000 --> 00:24:11,800
With Tangaballi.

321
00:24:13,040 --> 00:24:15,720
Yes, that is why I ran away!

322
00:24:15,880 --> 00:24:16,880
I didn't understand.

323
00:24:17,640 --> 00:24:20,480
Tangaballi is my father's friend's son.

324
00:24:21,520 --> 00:24:24,880
If I marry him then my father will
own his friend's village.

325
00:24:29,160 --> 00:24:31,240
That's why my father wants
to get me married.

326
00:24:42,920 --> 00:24:44,920
Did you understand
the entire situation?

327
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,520
No.

328
00:24:48,880 --> 00:24:51,000
No.

329
00:24:51,680 --> 00:24:55,640
It's your father, your goons,
your marriage! What's my fault?

330
00:24:57,040 --> 00:24:58,560
The problem is yours, your kidnapping

331
00:24:58,640 --> 00:25:01,680
that village is also yours
and it's my neck on the line?

332
00:25:02,040 --> 00:25:04,480
That means, what is yours is mine?

333
00:25:04,640 --> 00:25:06,400
No, Meenamma.

334
00:25:06,480 --> 00:25:10,800
People fly kites in the air! Your goons
throw mobiles and TCs in the air!

335
00:25:10,880 --> 00:25:13,040
I was happily going to Goa.

336
00:25:13,880 --> 00:25:15,960
Goa is on! But no!

337
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:20,560
Take the Chennai Express!

338
00:25:24,840 --> 00:25:25,920
I am ruined!

339
00:25:58,120 --> 00:26:00,920
<i>I thought of running away at night</i>

340
00:26:32,600 --> 00:26:36,040
<i>When I opened my
eyes in the morning...</i>

341
00:26:40,840 --> 00:26:41,760
Will you have some <i>Idli</i>?

342
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:42,640
No.

343
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:51,200
I need to go.

344
00:26:51,280 --> 00:26:52,880
- Will you eat?
- No, I'll go.

345
00:26:55,760 --> 00:26:57,200
Why is he not eating <i>Idli</i>?

346
00:27:04,760 --> 00:27:06,440
Inspector Sir...

347
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,200
Periya.

348
00:27:16,160 --> 00:27:17,160
What, officer?

349
00:27:18,080 --> 00:27:20,760
Did you hear the
sound of this chicken?

350
00:27:21,360 --> 00:27:22,240
What did he say?

351
00:27:22,360 --> 00:27:23,240
He said...

352
00:27:23,360 --> 00:27:25,240
Have you ever heard chickens?

353
00:27:30,560 --> 00:27:31,880
??

354
00:27:38,480 --> 00:27:39,640
Check if there anything to eat?

355
00:27:39,800 --> 00:27:40,840
Okay.

356
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:43,160
Meenamma.

357
00:27:43,880 --> 00:27:46,040
That policeman instead of
helping me, he...

358
00:27:46,880 --> 00:27:49,040
From here the entire region
belongs to my father.

359
00:27:49,800 --> 00:27:52,000
Even the policemen here takes
my father's help.

360
00:27:52,080 --> 00:27:53,000
What do you mean?

361
00:27:53,840 --> 00:27:57,440
It means that no one can do anything
to these four.

362
00:27:57,520 --> 00:27:59,800
That means from here
anything can happen to me?

363
00:28:00,120 --> 00:28:00,920
Yes.

364
00:28:01,040 --> 00:28:03,400
- Means I could even lose my life here?
- Yes

365
00:28:03,600 --> 00:28:05,520
What are you agreeing on?

366
00:28:05,600 --> 00:28:08,160
You should never tell
a dying person that he's about to die.

367
00:28:08,240 --> 00:28:11,760
At least give me some sort
of false hope that I will be safe.

368
00:28:13,880 --> 00:28:14,960
You can be saved.

369
00:28:18,800 --> 00:28:20,720
Now my ashes will also be immersed
as that of grandpa's.

370
00:28:20,800 --> 00:28:22,720
I don't know why did I give you my hand!

371
00:28:24,480 --> 00:28:25,800
You gave me your hand?

372
00:28:25,920 --> 00:28:28,920
In a bid to save myself I was running.
Why did you help them?

373
00:28:29,080 --> 00:28:31,120
Had I known that
your brothers were goons

374
00:28:31,200 --> 00:28:32,360
I would have kicked them instead
of helping them.

375
00:28:32,440 --> 00:28:33,880
Anyway, you are the root cause
of this entire problem.

376
00:28:34,000 --> 00:28:35,960
Ever since you've come into my life,
my life sucks!

377
00:28:44,680 --> 00:28:45,680
Why have you come to me?

378
00:28:46,280 --> 00:28:48,080
You came on my side!

379
00:28:48,160 --> 00:28:50,640
Forget about sides, Meenamma.
Come to the point.

380
00:28:51,480 --> 00:28:54,240
Is there any way for the two of us
to get out? Tell me, please!

381
00:28:55,160 --> 00:28:57,000
- Please!
- Yes, there is.

382
00:28:57,800 --> 00:28:58,840
What is it? Please tell me.

383
00:29:00,240 --> 00:29:03,120
But you will have to do as I say.

384
00:29:03,920 --> 00:29:05,760
As if everything was going
my way till now.

385
00:29:06,440 --> 00:29:08,120
I'll do it.
Tell me what has to be done?

386
00:29:10,000 --> 00:29:12,880
Once we reach Komban,
in front of my father...

387
00:29:12,960 --> 00:29:15,840
whenever I look towards you,
just nod your head.

388
00:29:17,000 --> 00:29:18,200
Nod what?

389
00:29:18,760 --> 00:29:19,560
Head.

390
00:29:19,640 --> 00:29:20,920
What?

391
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:24,840
Nod my head.

392
00:29:25,000 --> 00:29:26,880
Nod my head.

393
00:29:26,960 --> 00:29:28,600
I will eat <i>idli</i>, <i>dosa</i>.
I will nod my head.

394
00:29:28,680 --> 00:29:30,120
I will eat <i>dosa</i>...

395
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:35,200
Take the Chennai Express.

396
00:29:48,200 --> 00:29:49,040
Hey, Chinna.

397
00:29:49,360 --> 00:29:50,800
We reached. Come!

398
00:29:55,920 --> 00:29:57,040
Let's go.

399
00:29:57,640 --> 00:30:01,000
What are you doing, brother?
Meenamma, why did he pull the chain?

400
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:04,320
When we arrive at our village,
we pull the chain.

401
00:30:08,760 --> 00:30:11,520
We decide where the train station is.

402
00:30:11,640 --> 00:30:12,680
Come on!

403
00:30:13,680 --> 00:30:14,520
Come?

404
00:31:19,040 --> 00:31:20,480
Hey! Move on.

405
00:32:16,280 --> 00:32:17,160
Who is this?

406
00:32:19,040 --> 00:32:19,840
My father.

407
00:32:54,920 --> 00:32:57,160
How many times will you try to escape?

408
00:32:58,640 --> 00:33:01,280
Why are you doing this?
For what?

409
00:33:03,760 --> 00:33:04,560
I don't want to marry Tangaballi...

410
00:33:04,640 --> 00:33:07,200
<i>Meena was making her
father understand, emotionally.</i>

411
00:33:07,920 --> 00:33:09,560
<i>Her father was shocked
with what Meena was saying.</i>

412
00:33:09,680 --> 00:33:10,800
I am in love with somebody.

413
00:33:11,520 --> 00:33:12,320
Who is he?

414
00:33:12,400 --> 00:33:13,720
- <i>And I was...</i>
- Him.

415
00:33:13,800 --> 00:33:16,200
<i>And I was as clueless as you all are.</i>

416
00:33:17,400 --> 00:33:18,960
He loves me too.

417
00:33:21,880 --> 00:33:22,680
Am I right?

418
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:28,160
<i>The plan was to just nod my head.
That is why...</i>

419
00:33:31,880 --> 00:33:35,000
<i>After such a reaction,
one thing was certain.</i>

420
00:33:35,800 --> 00:33:37,440
<i>In the future, I wouldn't
be able to nod my head...</i>

421
00:33:37,520 --> 00:33:39,800
<i>because it won't be there!</i>

422
00:33:41,800 --> 00:33:43,120
My dear...

423
00:33:46,240 --> 00:33:48,240
Is Tamil your mother tongue?

424
00:33:51,040 --> 00:33:53,400
What is your father asking me
about my mother?

425
00:33:55,480 --> 00:33:58,000
He's asking you
if you know Tamil.

426
00:34:00,400 --> 00:34:03,720
Father, he is settled in the North.

427
00:34:04,400 --> 00:34:07,120
I will teach him Tamil
after our marriage.

428
00:34:07,240 --> 00:34:10,520
Meena likes this boy. Bring him.

429
00:34:26,239 --> 00:34:29,199
Meenamma, I thought
they were going to kill me.

430
00:34:29,560 --> 00:34:31,639
But your father's goons
lifted me up on their shoulders.

431
00:34:33,520 --> 00:34:34,679
What did you say to them?

432
00:34:34,760 --> 00:34:36,080
I just told them three lies.

433
00:34:36,239 --> 00:34:37,040
You lied?

434
00:34:37,120 --> 00:34:38,760
At least tell me
what you said, Ms Subtitle.

435
00:34:39,000 --> 00:34:41,800
My first lie was that we are very much
in love with each other.

436
00:34:43,360 --> 00:34:46,239
My second lie was that we wanted
to get married to each other.

437
00:34:47,840 --> 00:34:49,600
That's when you nodded your head.

438
00:34:49,679 --> 00:34:51,920
Yes, I nodded. But that...

439
00:34:52,080 --> 00:34:53,719
So, all of them have accepted this?

440
00:34:53,800 --> 00:34:54,760
No.

441
00:34:55,280 --> 00:34:58,160
The plan only worked when
I told them the third lie.

442
00:34:58,240 --> 00:34:59,040
What was that?

443
00:34:59,120 --> 00:35:01,320
That you lived in North
since you were a child,

444
00:35:01,480 --> 00:35:03,240
which is why you
don't know Tamil.

445
00:35:03,320 --> 00:35:05,560
He thought my story was genuine.

446
00:35:05,640 --> 00:35:08,840
That's why they're taking us
to the village to decide our future.

447
00:35:08,960 --> 00:35:11,400
Not to decide on the future but
to destroy my future.

448
00:35:12,520 --> 00:35:13,320
Hey, brother!

449
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:16,000
Think about it Rahul,
I will get married.

450
00:35:17,280 --> 00:35:18,080
Brother!

451
00:35:18,160 --> 00:35:20,200
At first there were four
of them running after you.

452
00:35:20,520 --> 00:35:22,640
Now the whole village will chase you.

453
00:35:23,600 --> 00:35:25,960
I did this drama so we could
buy some time.

454
00:35:26,040 --> 00:35:28,440
We will run away as soon
as we get an opportunity at night.

455
00:35:28,520 --> 00:35:29,320
Run away...

456
00:35:30,760 --> 00:35:32,560
I have a lot of experience
in running away.

457
00:36:15,200 --> 00:36:19,440
<i>Meena's family reminded me
of the population in China.</i>

458
00:36:19,920 --> 00:36:22,520
<i>Meena began telling them the story
of Chennai Express.</i>

459
00:36:22,680 --> 00:36:26,520
<i>As the story progressed, everyone seemed
to be impressed with me.</i>

460
00:36:26,600 --> 00:36:27,800
<i>But I was depressed.</i>

461
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:29,200
<i>I was stressed.</i>

462
00:36:29,280 --> 00:36:34,600
<i>Because the place where I had arrived
was a very dangerous one!</i>

463
00:36:41,360 --> 00:36:43,720
<i>Everyone was treating me well.</i>

464
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:47,600
<i>But a goat is also well fed before
it is sacrificed!</i>

465
00:36:55,520 --> 00:36:58,280
I've asked Bobby to get a fancy number
at times but...

466
00:36:58,520 --> 00:37:02,200
<i>The numbers I was trying to call</i>

467
00:37:02,320 --> 00:37:04,800
<i>Were all washed away from my brain.</i>

468
00:37:05,760 --> 00:37:09,240
<i>The mobile technology definitely
connected us with our closed ones but...</i>

469
00:37:09,640 --> 00:37:12,240
<i>It had also messed
with our heads.</i>

470
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:13,760
<i>At first when there were
no mobile phones</i>

471
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:15,240
<i>Then we would remember
all telephone numbers.</i>

472
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:18,440
<i>Now that we have a mobile phone
we don't remember any numbers!</i>

473
00:37:19,320 --> 00:37:20,200
Meena...

474
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:22,680
What's the plan to get out of here?

475
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:28,880
Meena, don't ignore me.

476
00:37:28,960 --> 00:37:31,360
This drama has gone on for too long,
it's quite enough now.

477
00:37:31,440 --> 00:37:32,360
- I'm losing patience.
- Rahul.

478
00:37:34,120 --> 00:37:34,920
Hello, Sir.

479
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:42,160
- Get him a coffee.
- Get it.

480
00:38:11,560 --> 00:38:14,080
The food is ready. Call everybody.

481
00:38:23,880 --> 00:38:25,360
Madhi, come here.

482
00:38:50,480 --> 00:38:51,440
Rahul.

483
00:38:53,280 --> 00:38:54,160
Rahul.

484
00:39:20,440 --> 00:39:21,360
Oh, no!

485
00:39:34,920 --> 00:39:36,400
Hey, you are so smart.

486
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:38,560
What are you jabbering in Tamil?
Talk in Hindi.

487
00:39:38,640 --> 00:39:40,640
Hey, you are very beautiful.

488
00:39:40,760 --> 00:39:44,160
You learnt Tamil in a day?

489
00:39:46,480 --> 00:39:48,720
Meena, I am not
this sort of a guy. Please!

490
00:39:53,640 --> 00:39:54,440
- Meena.
- Rahul.

491
00:39:54,520 --> 00:39:55,720
- Madhi.
- Puvi.

492
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:01,440
They came.

493
00:40:01,640 --> 00:40:04,720
We just followed them.

494
00:40:05,080 --> 00:40:06,080
Yes.

495
00:40:06,640 --> 00:40:07,560
