744
00:55:45,080 --> 00:55:47,360
We're going to Sri Lanka
with the smuggle diesel.

745
00:55:49,840 --> 00:55:51,600
Everything is legal
when one has to survive.

746
00:55:51,680 --> 00:55:53,280
If the Sri Lanka Marine police catch us,
we will be jailed.

747
00:55:53,360 --> 00:55:55,320
If the Indian Marine police catch us,
we will be jailed here.

748
00:55:55,400 --> 00:55:58,320
If police don't catch us,
all is well.

749
00:55:58,880 --> 00:56:00,000
Oil is well!

750
00:56:02,840 --> 00:56:04,120
Shut up and stop the boat.

751
00:56:07,440 --> 00:56:09,000
Help me!
I've got on to the wrong boat.

752
00:56:10,800 --> 00:56:13,840
- Bring out the gun.
- Help me.

753
00:56:14,560 --> 00:56:15,360
Gun!

754
00:56:39,280 --> 00:56:40,240
Enough.

755
00:56:46,600 --> 00:56:48,280
Catch them and arrest them.

756
00:56:48,680 --> 00:56:51,440
You're the first smuggler who is
so happy about being arrested.

757
00:56:52,040 --> 00:56:52,880
No, Sir.

758
00:56:52,960 --> 00:56:53,760
I'm not a smuggler.

759
00:56:53,840 --> 00:56:54,840
I am not with them, Sir.

760
00:56:54,920 --> 00:56:55,920
I am an Indian, Sir.

761
00:56:56,120 --> 00:56:58,080
Is it? Show me your passport!

762
00:56:58,760 --> 00:57:00,000
Passport? Why, Sir?

763
00:57:00,080 --> 00:57:02,520
To verify whether you are
an Indian or Sri Lankan.

764
00:57:05,080 --> 00:57:06,520
But Sir, I am not with them.

765
00:57:06,800 --> 00:57:08,720
I speak Hindi, Sir!

766
00:57:08,840 --> 00:57:10,520
We can also talk in Hindi.

767
00:57:10,920 --> 00:57:13,000
Listen. Hindi!

768
00:57:13,560 --> 00:57:14,360
What?

769
00:57:14,440 --> 00:57:15,720
We all speak in Hindi!

770
00:57:15,800 --> 00:57:17,120
Sir, he's my man.

771
00:57:17,200 --> 00:57:18,320
And you are my wife!

772
00:57:18,400 --> 00:57:19,200
What?

773
00:57:23,120 --> 00:57:24,600
What are you looking at?
Arrest him.

774
00:57:24,880 --> 00:57:25,840
What does that mean?

775
00:57:28,240 --> 00:57:31,440
<i>They say if you suffix word Ji,
to any other word</i>

776
00:57:31,520 --> 00:57:32,400
<i>You gain respect.</i>

777
00:57:33,080 --> 00:57:34,960
<i>Refu... Ji.</i>

778
00:57:35,080 --> 00:57:36,480
<i>I did not gain anything!</i>

779
00:57:37,080 --> 00:57:40,760
<i>Here my fate was being written by
my grandpa sitting in heavens</i>

780
00:57:41,040 --> 00:57:44,280
<i>Whereas Meena's fate
was being written by her father.</i>

781
00:57:45,160 --> 00:57:48,680
<i>He decided to get her
married to Tangaballi.</i>

782
00:57:49,040 --> 00:57:51,760
<i>Meena was neither happy
with it nor was it her choice.</i>

783
00:57:52,960 --> 00:57:55,560
<i>Who would have thought
That the tip of India</i>

784
00:57:55,800 --> 00:58:00,240
<i>Would begin a new chapter
In Meena's and my life.</i>

785
00:58:21,760 --> 00:58:25,000
Brother, what are you looking at
with such fear?

786
00:58:25,200 --> 00:58:26,440
- Is this yours?
- Yes.

787
00:58:26,520 --> 00:58:28,320
I'm sure there is RDX in it.

788
00:58:28,480 --> 00:58:30,360
Not "there is."
There was.

789
00:58:30,480 --> 00:58:31,560
I mean, there was!

790
00:58:31,640 --> 00:58:32,760
My grandpa is in it.

791
00:58:32,840 --> 00:58:34,160
I mean my grandpa's ashes.

792
00:58:34,240 --> 00:58:35,040
Allow me to show you.

793
00:58:38,600 --> 00:58:40,560
I have been telling you that
I am not a smuggler!

794
00:58:48,080 --> 00:58:52,320
You know, Sir. I came from Mumbai
to immerse my grandpa's ashes. That's all.

795
00:58:53,760 --> 00:58:55,040
<i>I told the police everything truthfully.</i>

796
00:58:55,440 --> 00:58:57,520
<i>My history.
The geography of my travel.</i>

797
00:58:57,600 --> 00:58:59,560
<i>And my chemistry
with the people of Komban.</i>

798
00:58:59,640 --> 00:59:02,560
<i>After hearing all this, all
the Marine police officer said was...</i>

799
00:59:03,120 --> 00:59:05,120
So, the people of Komban know you, right?

800
00:59:47,560 --> 00:59:48,360
Sir!

801
00:59:48,440 --> 00:59:49,440
You!

802
00:59:50,880 --> 00:59:52,560
Your fellow brothers are dropping
me to Mumbai.

803
00:59:52,640 --> 00:59:53,600
Give me a hug!

804
00:59:54,280 --> 00:59:56,440
You left me there, right?

805
00:59:56,760 --> 00:59:58,920
Because of some smugglers
I went away to Sri Lanka.

806
00:59:59,000 --> 00:59:59,880
You didn't go away. You came back...

807
00:59:59,960 --> 01:00:00,920
- to Komban.
- No, I can't come.

808
01:00:01,000 --> 01:00:02,480
How can that happen?

809
01:00:02,560 --> 01:00:03,880
Look...

810
01:00:12,280 --> 01:00:14,040
I'll be back.

811
01:00:15,120 --> 01:00:15,920
Brother, me too.

812
01:00:16,040 --> 01:00:17,000
Catch him.

813
01:00:17,200 --> 01:00:18,280
What are you doing, man?

814
01:00:19,880 --> 01:00:23,000
Sir, please leave me for heaven's sake!

815
01:00:24,320 --> 01:00:25,160
Hello, Sir.

816
01:00:25,640 --> 01:00:26,680
Hello.

817
01:00:27,840 --> 01:00:28,920
Do you know him?

818
01:00:29,760 --> 01:00:31,200
Do we know him?

819
01:00:31,280 --> 01:00:34,560
We know him.

820
01:00:35,360 --> 01:00:37,000
- Periya.
- Yes.

821
01:00:37,080 --> 01:00:38,120
He is our family member, isn't it?

822
01:00:38,240 --> 01:00:41,440
Yes, he is one of us.

823
01:00:41,680 --> 01:00:43,560
Hey, where had you disappeared?

824
01:00:44,280 --> 01:00:46,920
There's such tension
since you went missing.

825
01:00:47,520 --> 01:00:49,760
Oh, family!
So you are an Indian after all.

826
01:00:49,840 --> 01:00:51,800
I will release you here and leave.

827
01:00:51,880 --> 01:00:53,840
Officer, you cannot leave me here and go.

828
01:00:55,080 --> 01:00:57,480
I am Sri... Devi

829
01:01:01,320 --> 01:01:03,080
"How are you, my darling?"

830
01:01:03,680 --> 01:01:04,640
Refree, right?

831
01:01:04,720 --> 01:01:06,600
No, Sir. I meant, Periyathalai Sir...

832
01:01:06,720 --> 01:01:08,680
Hanger, right?

833
01:01:08,760 --> 01:01:10,000
I meant strong, Sir.

834
01:01:10,080 --> 01:01:11,360
You called me fat?

835
01:01:12,080 --> 01:01:13,280
Chewing gum, right?

836
01:01:18,760 --> 01:01:20,400
Do not step ahead.
I am warning you.

837
01:01:20,480 --> 01:01:22,680
I will cut down all!

838
01:01:22,840 --> 01:01:24,080
Hold this.

839
01:01:25,120 --> 01:01:26,800
Nobody steps ahead.

840
01:01:26,960 --> 01:01:30,040
If anybody comes forward, I will...

841
01:01:30,520 --> 01:01:32,360
cut myself.

842
01:01:32,520 --> 01:01:33,560
Okay, cut yourself.

843
01:01:34,920 --> 01:01:35,920
Cut yourself.

844
01:01:36,400 --> 01:01:38,280
I will cut Meenamma.

845
01:01:58,760 --> 01:01:59,560
Stop.

846
01:02:01,880 --> 01:02:03,440
I will cut Meenamma.

847
01:02:06,600 --> 01:02:08,800
Meenamma, open the door.

848
01:02:10,680 --> 01:02:11,800
Nobody moves!

849
01:02:16,800 --> 01:02:17,640
Move!

850
01:02:19,360 --> 01:02:21,280
What do I do, Meenamma?

851
01:02:27,880 --> 01:02:28,840
Catch him.

852
01:03:20,840 --> 01:03:22,080
Come on, get out.

853
01:03:23,360 --> 01:03:25,880
First you get drunk and run away
all by yourself.

854
01:03:26,000 --> 01:03:28,520
Then you get into trouble
and use me to run away.

855
01:03:28,600 --> 01:03:29,400
And now you're asking me
to get out of the car!

856
01:03:29,480 --> 01:03:31,000
Yes, that's what I said.
Get out, please.

857
01:03:31,080 --> 01:03:31,880
I won't get out.

858
01:03:31,960 --> 01:03:33,000
This car belongs to my father.

859
01:03:33,080 --> 01:03:34,680
If you don't get out,
I will take you back there.

860
01:03:34,760 --> 01:03:35,920
Then you'll get married.

861
01:03:36,000 --> 01:03:38,400
Before that, from Rahul you
will become Late Rahul.

862
01:03:39,320 --> 01:03:41,320
I mean I think there's no parking here.
Let's go.

863
01:03:56,520 --> 01:03:57,560
Rahul!

864
01:05:46,960 --> 01:05:48,680
What happened? Has the
car broken down?

865
01:05:49,840 --> 01:05:51,360
No! Who told you that?

866
01:05:53,080 --> 01:05:53,880
What is with the smoke, then?

867
01:05:53,960 --> 01:05:54,800
Smoke?

868
01:05:54,920 --> 01:05:56,440
The car is smoking a cigarette.

869
01:05:56,520 --> 01:05:57,760
And do you know why I came outside?

870
01:05:57,840 --> 01:06:00,880
I thought to myself, that I could wait and
relax here and Tangaballi would come by.

871
01:06:00,960 --> 01:06:03,760
And, when he comes, the three
of us can play together.

872
01:06:04,640 --> 01:06:05,520
Can't you see?

873
01:06:06,160 --> 01:06:08,360
Your father's car is even worse
than your Hindi.

874
01:06:08,440 --> 01:06:09,520
You have wrecked the car!

875
01:06:09,600 --> 01:06:11,600
Don't call this a car,
it'd be a sin to call this a car.

876
01:06:11,680 --> 01:06:13,200
This car has saved your life.

877
01:06:13,280 --> 01:06:15,280
It's not a car, it's a wreck!

878
01:06:17,080 --> 01:06:18,440
My father's favorite car!

879
01:06:25,400 --> 01:06:27,400
Catch it, Rahul!

880
01:06:27,480 --> 01:06:29,960
I didn't mean it. Wait!

881
01:06:42,480 --> 01:06:44,000
- No!
- Oh, no!

882
01:06:56,680 --> 01:06:57,480
Take it!

883
01:06:58,240 --> 01:07:00,280
Take it, Meenamma baby.

884
01:07:00,400 --> 01:07:02,120
Your father's favorite car.

885
01:07:02,200 --> 01:07:04,520
Actually the problem is not your father,
or his wrecked car.

886
01:07:04,600 --> 01:07:05,520
The problem is you.

887
01:07:05,640 --> 01:07:08,640
Wherever you go, you carry
a free trouble pack along with you.

888
01:07:09,200 --> 01:07:10,320
Actually you are like a black cat.

889
01:07:11,400 --> 01:07:12,760
Worse than a black cat!

890
01:07:12,840 --> 01:07:15,600
If you cross the path of a black cat,
it will get cursed.

891
01:07:16,480 --> 01:07:17,400
Then why are you with me?

892
01:07:17,480 --> 01:07:18,520
Why am I with you?

893
01:07:18,600 --> 01:07:19,960
Why are you with me?

894
01:07:20,080 --> 01:07:22,000
Please, Meenamma.
Stop stalking me.

895
01:07:25,040 --> 01:07:25,840
Alright.

896
01:07:27,120 --> 01:07:29,720
But by the way, you stole the car and
drove in the wrong direction.

897
01:07:29,800 --> 01:07:31,720
Now we have only one way out.

898
01:07:31,840 --> 01:07:34,080
We'll have to cross Komban again!

899
01:07:34,200 --> 01:07:35,520
Don't scare me with Komban.

900
01:07:35,600 --> 01:07:38,400
If you are not with me,
I will manage on my own easily.

901
01:07:39,000 --> 01:07:41,960
There's no word called impossible
in my dictionary.

902
01:07:42,080 --> 01:07:45,000
Really? From where did you buy such
a rubbish dictionary?

903
01:07:51,480 --> 01:07:52,520
Get lost.

904
01:08:01,640 --> 01:08:05,160
<i>I thought I would not meet
Meenamma ever again.</i>

905
01:08:05,920 --> 01:08:08,440
<i>But fate had decreed
something else altogether.</i>

906
01:08:25,040 --> 01:08:26,160
Brother.

907
01:09:09,200 --> 01:09:10,240
Hello, Sir.

908
01:09:11,240 --> 01:09:13,439
I need to find the road.

909
01:09:14,279 --> 01:09:17,760
Where is the highway?

910
01:09:25,200 --> 01:09:26,200
What are you doing?

911
01:09:26,800 --> 01:09:30,200
I want to see the road.

912
01:09:32,920 --> 01:09:34,840
Where is the highway?

913
01:09:35,359 --> 01:09:37,200
Where is the highway?

914
01:09:56,680 --> 01:09:58,480
Relax, my child!

915
01:09:59,720 --> 01:10:01,800
Don't take so much trouble.
I feel bad, then.

916
01:10:04,080 --> 01:10:05,960
The two of us have the same problem.

917
01:10:06,120 --> 01:10:08,080
At this age, we don't need
a new language.

918
01:10:37,480 --> 01:10:38,920
Hey, brother!

919
01:10:41,800 --> 01:10:43,520
Please, stop.

920
01:10:46,160 --> 01:10:48,000
Hello, brother!

921
01:10:48,080 --> 01:10:49,760
What do you want?
What is your work here?

922
01:10:51,800 --> 01:10:53,920
I'm a boy, Rahul.
I need a lift!

923
01:10:54,840 --> 01:10:56,480
You're from Mumbai, right?

924
01:10:57,240 --> 01:10:58,560
How do you know so much about me?

925
01:10:58,680 --> 01:11:00,680
The entire South knows you.

926
01:11:00,760 --> 01:11:05,360
One fair boy has eloped with Durgeshwara
Azagsundaram's daughter in a car.

927
01:11:05,480 --> 01:11:07,760
Oh my God!

928
01:11:07,920 --> 01:11:10,000
Today you are in a car tomorrow
you will be the headline of a newspaper.

929
01:11:10,200 --> 01:11:11,440
- No, listen to me.
- Go away.

930
01:11:11,920 --> 01:11:15,080
You don't know, the village people
are chasing you with sticks!

931
01:11:15,200 --> 01:11:19,560
Once you're caught they will kill you
and put that as a headline!

932
01:11:19,800 --> 01:11:22,240
Let it be. Is it their kingdom?

933
01:11:22,360 --> 01:11:25,920
The girl you have eloped with,
this is her father's kingdom!

934
01:11:26,000 --> 01:11:27,160
Brother, please help me.

935
01:11:27,280 --> 01:11:30,360
- Go away.
- Brother, please.

936
01:11:30,680 --> 01:11:31,960
Brother, help me.

937
01:11:34,720 --> 01:11:35,760
Brother!

938
01:11:38,920 --> 01:11:42,640
<i>I became numb after hearing this.</i>

939
01:11:44,200 --> 01:11:45,800
<i>I could see the road ahead</i>

940
01:11:46,400 --> 01:11:48,560
<i>But there was no way out.</i>

941
01:11:49,720 --> 01:11:51,400
<i>Except one.</i>

942
01:11:52,400 --> 01:11:54,480
Meenamma...

943
01:11:57,320 --> 01:11:59,280
Meenamma...

944
01:11:59,400 --> 01:12:01,440
Meenamma...

945
01:12:01,680 --> 01:12:03,040
Meenamma...

946
01:12:06,800 --> 01:12:07,600
What is it?

947
01:12:07,680 --> 01:12:08,840
What?

948
01:12:09,640 --> 01:12:11,160
You've come back to me after all!

949
01:12:12,440 --> 01:12:15,240
You figured out how does it feel
to live alone, didn't you?

950
01:12:15,440 --> 01:12:16,760
Look at your face.

951
01:12:16,840 --> 01:12:19,480
It seems like you are getting
a fever because you are so frightened.

952
01:12:20,160 --> 01:12:22,160
Come on.
I've come to take you.

953
01:12:22,640 --> 01:12:24,880
We will go together. Come!

954
01:12:26,960 --> 01:12:28,960
Again you've taken the wrong route.

955
01:12:29,160 --> 01:12:31,480
This is the safer route.
That side you will find Tangaballi.

956
01:12:31,680 --> 01:12:32,480
Come on!

957
01:12:33,880 --> 01:12:35,880
Meenamma, I'll save you.

958
01:13:20,880 --> 01:13:22,040
Vidamba village.

959
01:13:23,120 --> 01:13:24,000
Come on.

960
01:13:37,640 --> 01:13:39,800
A wedding ceremony is going on here.

961
01:13:39,880 --> 01:13:41,760
If we make up a story

962
01:13:42,240 --> 01:13:44,080
we can stay here for a few days.

963
01:13:44,440 --> 01:13:47,520
Until then father and Tangaballi's tension
will get a bit diffused.

964
01:13:47,600 --> 01:13:50,040
Then why are you standing here
and talking, Ms. Subtitle?

965
01:13:50,160 --> 01:13:51,520
Go ahead and talk to them.

966
01:13:53,280 --> 01:13:54,360
Such attitude!

967
01:13:54,440 --> 01:13:55,640
Why don't you go and talk?

968
01:13:55,720 --> 01:13:56,800
I can.

969
01:13:56,880 --> 01:13:58,400
I know <i>kunjam kunjam</i>.

970
01:13:58,520 --> 01:14:00,480
<i>"Apadiya sapadiya Po."</i>

971
01:14:01,480 --> 01:14:03,400
Your grandpa can go take a hike!

972
01:14:04,080 --> 01:14:05,520
You know how to speak Marathi?

973
01:14:05,600 --> 01:14:08,400
If you can speak Tamil, why can't
I speak Marathi?

974
01:14:08,480 --> 01:14:11,840
Oh, mother! Meenamma,
for now just go and talk in Tamil.

975
01:14:19,160 --> 01:14:23,680
<i>It seemed very pleasant but
there was something fishy.</i>

976
01:14:24,080 --> 01:14:27,640
<i>There was something definitely fishy.</i>

977
01:14:37,400 --> 01:14:40,280
<i>Once bitten, twice shy.</i>

978
01:14:40,520 --> 01:14:43,960
<i>That's why, this time
I did not nod in agreement.</i>

979
01:14:53,040 --> 01:14:58,880
<i>The second time when the villagers
looked at me, I...</i>

980
01:15:01,640 --> 01:15:02,760
What happened?

981
01:15:04,040 --> 01:15:06,680
Hey! Don't come to me.

982
01:15:29,040 --> 01:15:31,040
Open the window.
Let the fresh air come in.

983
01:15:32,400 --> 01:15:34,760
Here is the towel and some clothes.

984
01:15:34,880 --> 01:15:36,800
Rest well.

985
01:15:36,880 --> 01:15:40,720
In the morning, after your bath,
we will arrange the prayers.

986
01:15:41,680 --> 01:15:44,920
Rest well. Take care of him. Bye.

987
01:15:46,200 --> 01:15:48,280
You know, a film should be made on me.

988
01:15:48,480 --> 01:15:49,960
I laugh my way into a mess.

989
01:15:50,160 --> 01:15:53,200
Whenever people gladly lift me up on
their shoulders, I know I am in a trouble.

990
01:15:53,320 --> 01:15:54,320
And you, Meenamma...

991
01:15:56,840 --> 01:15:58,360
What are the lies you have
spun around this time?

992
01:15:58,920 --> 01:16:01,640
I told them we got married and ran away.

993
01:16:01,880 --> 01:16:05,880
Have you copyrighted this story
of getting married and running away?

994
01:16:09,760 --> 01:16:10,680
Then what did you say?

995
01:16:12,880 --> 01:16:17,680
The second lie was that you're so good
that you will never leave me and go.

996
01:16:18,680 --> 01:16:22,960
Then you agreed to me.

997
01:16:23,280 --> 01:16:24,080
Yes.

998
01:16:24,600 --> 01:16:29,120
Then I said you got so tired
with the journey

999
01:16:29,200 --> 01:16:32,200
that you felt like fainting.

